At least 16 people were killed in a horror crash on the N3 South in Pietermaritzburg early this morning. Zinhle Mngomezulu from the Road Traffic Inspectorate is on the scene. #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - At least 16 people were killed in a horror crash on the N3 south in Pietermaritzburg early on Saturday morning. A fully-loaded taxi burst into flames in a multi-vehicle collision with another taxi, two trucks, a bakkie and five cars. READ: Dozens feared dead after horror crash on N3 When emergency services arrived, the fire spread to other vehicles. There was also a secondary crash on the northbound carriageway. READ: N3 South in Pietermaritzburg reopens following deadly crash KwaZulu-Natal traffic authorities are on the scene. The road is open, but officials are asking for patience due to slow traffic.